ooking to dining-have created new cooks, new cooking categories, and new culinary challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aCookingzUnited StatesxHistory. 4aamateur cooks. 4aamerican cooking. 4aamerican cuisine. 4aanthropology of food. 4achefs. 4acooking at home. 4acooking skills. 4acreative process. 4aculinary challenges. 4adining. 4afood and relationships. 4ahome cooking. 4ameal prep. 4arelationships with food. 4ashopping. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520963979423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780520963979.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles